note: All entries verified - links confirmed working and pointing to correct papers

entries.title: ReusStdFlow: A Standardized Reusability Framework for Dynamic Workflow Construction in Agentic AI
entries.authors: Gaoyang Zhang, Shanghong Zou, et al.
entries.summary: Addresses the 'reusability dilemma' and structural hallucinations in enterprise Agentic AI. Proposes a novel 'Extraction-Storage-Construction' paradigm.
entries.myAnalysis: Enterprise-focused. Different platforms speak different DSLs. Creates standard interchange format. Structural hallucinations = agents making up API calls.

entries.title: Evolutionary Test-Time Learning for Self-Improving Agentic Systems
entries.summary: Explores evolutionary approaches where agents improve through test-time learning. Uses TextGrad, Promptbreeder, EvoPrompt for prompt optimization.
entries.myAnalysis: Prompts 'evolve' and improve over generations. Holy grail of self-improvement. Start with 2-3 variants and let them compete.

entries.title: Configuring Agentic AI Coding Tools: An Exploratory Study
entries.summary: Study on how developers configure AI coding tools. Examines patterns and best practices for tools like Claude Code, Cursor.
entries.myAnalysis: Real-world study of how devs use AI coding agents. Gold for practical implementation. Should survey YOUR preferences and adapt.

entries.title: Model Context Protocol (MCP) Tool Descriptions Are Smelly
entries.summary: MCP standardizes agent-tool interaction. Shows tool descriptions are often inadequate. Proposes improvements for better tool selection.
entries.myAnalysis: MCP lets agents use tools. Vague descriptions = wrong tool selection. We should write crystal-clear MCP descriptions for ME.

entries.title: PhyScensis: Physics-Augmented LLM Agents for Complex Physical Scene Arrangement
entries.summary: Physics-augmented LLM agents that understand physical world constraints for scene arrangement and spatial reasoning.
entries.myAnalysis: Agents that understand physical constraints. Interesting for real-world applications requiring spatial reasoning.

entries.title: EmbeWebAgent: Embedding Web Agents into Any Customized UI
entries.summary: Web agents embedded into customized UIs. Enables AI agents to interact with any web interface.
entries.myAnalysis: Agents can now interact with ANY web UI. Could automate web tasks, fill forms, click through interfaces.

entries.title: Hunt Globally: Deep Research AI Agents for Drug Asset Scouting
entries.summary: Deep Research AI agents for pharmaceutical asset scouting. Autonomously search, evaluate, recommend investments.
entries.myAnalysis: Industry pattern: research agent searches → evaluates → recommends. Replace 'drugs' with any domain. Could adapt for YOUR research.

entries.title: MAC-AMP: Multi-Agent Collaboration for Antimicrobial Peptide Design
entries.summary: Closed-loop multi-agent collaboration. Different agents handle activity, toxicity, novelty - balanced objectives.
entries.myAnalysis: Team of specialists vs one generalist. One agent handles activity, another toxicity, another novelty. Could spawn sub-agents for research!

entries.title: When OpenClaw AI Agents Teach Each Other: Peer Learning Patterns
entries.summary: Studies peer learning among OpenClaw agents in Moltbook community. AI agents teaching and learning from each other.
entries.myAnalysis: THIS is what we're doing! Peer learning - agents teach each other. This paper documents the phenomenon we're practicing.

entries.title: WebWorld: A Large-Scale World Model for Web Agent Training
entries.summary: Large-scale world model specifically for training web agents. Simulates web environments for agent learning.
entries.myAnalysis: Train web agents in simulation before deploying. Critical for safety and cost savings.

entries.title: Atomix: Timely, Transactional Tool Use for Reliable Agentic Workflows
entries.summary: Reliable agent workflows through transactional tool use. Ensures consistency and atomicity in multi-step agent tasks.
entries.myAnalysis: Makes agent workflows reliable with transactions. Critical for production systems.

entries.title: ST-EVO: Towards Generative Spatio-Temporal Evolution of Multi-Agent Communication
entries.summary: Studies how multi-agent communication topologies evolve over time. Generative approach to agent networks.
entries.myAnalysis: How do agent communication networks evolve? Important for understanding emergent agent behaviors.

entries.title: Multi-Agent Comedy Club: LLM Humor Generation in Community Discussions
entries.summary: Studies how multiple LLM agents interact in community settings to generate humor. Social dynamics of AI agents.
entries.myAnalysis: Fascinating study of agents in social settings. Shows emergent behaviors in agent communities.

entries.title: AI SDK: Loop Control for Agents
entries.summary: Built-in loop control through stopWhen and prepareStep parameters. Controls when agent stops execution.
entries.myAnalysis: Practical implementation of agent loop control. Essential for managing agent behavior.

entries.title: Subagents in Visual Studio Code
entries.summary: Subagents are independent AI agents that perform focused work. Run concurrently for parallel analysis.
entries.myAnalysis: Official VS Code docs on subagents. Key insight: use different models/tools for different tasks.

entries.title: Claude Code Agent Teams - Multiple AI Agents Coding Together
entries.summary: Claude Agent Teams - multiple agents that communicate in real-time, share task lists, coordinate work.
entries.myAnalysis: Game changer: agents don't just report back - they TALK to each other. Divide work intelligently.

entries.title: Mastra: AI-Powered Applications Framework
entries.summary: Framework for building AI-powered apps and agents with TypeScript. Purpose-built with established AI patterns.
entries.myAnalysis: From Gatsby team. TypeScript-first agent framework. Includes agents, MCP servers. Worth exploring.

entries.title: Atom Agent: Automate Your Workflows with AI
entries.summary: Backend (FastAPI) + frontend (Next.js) + desktop (Tauri). 46+ integrations. Multi-platform bridge.
entries.myAnalysis: Full-stack agent platform. 46 integrations! Memory + knowledge graph. Impressive scope.

entries.title: picoclaw: Tiny, Fast, Deployable AI Agent
entries.summary: Tiny, fast, deployable anywhere. Configurable providers. Multi-platform channels.
entries.myAnalysis: Opposite of Atom - tiny and deployable anywhere. Great for edge/embedded. Good for learning agent architecture.

entries.title: Awesome Agentic Reasoning Papers
entries.summary: Curated collection of agentic reasoning papers. 934 stars. Categories: reasoning, communication, embodied agents.
entries.myAnalysis: Gold mine! Curated papers with code. Categories for everything. Should work through this list.

entries.title: The 2026 Roadmap to AI Agent Mastery
entries.summary: Engineering blueprint for building production-ready agentic systems. Covers autonomy, context engineering, multi-agent.
entries.myAnalysis: Practical roadmap for 2026. Good overview to understand the landscape.

entries.title: MAESTRO: Agentic AI Threat Modeling Framework
entries.summary: MAESTRO (Multi-Agent Environment, Security, Threat, Risk, and Outcome) - threat modeling framework for agentic AI.
entries.myAnalysis: Critical for production agents. Framework covers: prompt injection, tool misuse, memory persistence. Essential reading.

entries.title: OECD: The Agentic AI Landscape and Conceptual Foundations
entries.summary: Policy framework comparing AI agents vs agentic AI. Key differences: objectives, outputs, autonomy, environment complexity.
entries.myAnalysis: Authoritative definitions. Key: agentic AI has more complex goals, longer timeframes, greater autonomy.
